The University College Hospital (UCH), Ibadan, has restricted mobility into its premises due to the COVID-19 outbreak in Oyo state, an official statement revealed.   In a circular by the Director of Administration, S.O. Oladejo, transmitted to all members of staff, the management directed that only staff who are car owners and have patients in the ward, will be allowed to enter the hospital in order curtail the spread of the coronavirus within UCH community. The statement dated March 23rd 2020 further emphasized that the limited staff will only be allowed entry upon display of their UCHâ€™s sticker on their private vehicles.